#: Game.Levels.Prado.L09_ExistsUnique
msgid ""
"§0 is notation for 'there exists exactly one §1 for which §2 holds'.\n"
"It is defined as 'There exists a §3 , s.t., §4 holds, and each other element "
"§5, for which\n"
"§6 holds, is equal to §7'. Try finding an appropriate §8 and apply §9"
msgstr ""
"**You**: I see – so §0 is notation for “there is exactly one §1 for which §2 "
"holds”.\n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Exactly. And by definition, that means „there exists a §3 such "
"that (1) §4 holds, and (2) every other element §5 for which §6 holds is "
"already equal to §7“. So the first step is to find a suitable §8 and to use "
"§9."

