#: Game.Levels.Saturn
#, fuzzy
msgid "Intro Saturn"
msgstr ""
"You didn't actually want to head for this planet. But your mind wasn't "
"entirely on the task at hand. And you can't afford to be inattentive in "
"universes, especially when you're unfamiliar with them. Now you've flown too "
"close, the gravity is too strong, and your regenerative drive is currently "
"in regeneration mode.\n"
"\n"
"**You**: What is that orange sauce on this planet? **Scribble**: It looks "
"rather toxic. Or hot.\n"
"\n"
"**You**: Or both. I really don't want to land there! **Scribble**: Yes, yes, "
"I'm doing my best. And look how much rubbish is already orbiting here! The "
"best we can do right now is fly with the current."

#: Game.Levels.Cantor
#, fuzzy
msgid "Intro Cantor"
msgstr ""
"You have landed next to a large tent. Perhaps a circus tent? It is quite "
"dark inside. Only the stage is brightly lit. On it stands a gentleman who "
"looks like a mixture of a professor and a magician, giving a monologue and "
"apparently performing something. In the semi-darkness in front of the stage, "
"chairs are arranged in long rows.\n"
"You have apparently entered the tent right at one end of the first row. The "
"row is so long that you cannot see the other end. And behind it are many "
"more rows – you cannot see the end of them either. But all the seats are "
"empty. So you sit down somewhere in the first row, look at the stage and "
"prick up your ears."

