#: Game.Levels.Quantus
#, fuzzy
msgid "Intro Quantus"
msgstr ""
"A large gathering of formal philosophers is already waiting for you on "
"Quantus. They are all talking wildly at once and you are having trouble "
"making yourself heard. Scribble finally produces a loud gong sound, which "
"briefly silences them.\n"
"\n"
"**You**: We have a letter for your queen. Could you take us to her? **All** "
"*(in unison)*: We're all here! **You**: Okay. Which one of you is the queen? "
"An awkward silence ensues. Everyone shrugs their shoulders.\n"
"\n"
"**You**: Do you even have a queen? **All** *(in unison)*: Yes, yes. We have "
"a queen, we have a queen. **Scribble** *(to you)*: Let me summarise. There "
"is a queen, but no one knows who she is... **You**: Isn't that a "
"contradiction?\n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Are you asking that as a mathematician? No, it's not a "
"contradiction. It's simply a \"pure statement of existence\". You're not "
"quite sure how serious he is. **You**: Then I suggest we simply hand the "
"parcel over to *all* the residents. Then we will have handed it over to the "
"queen in particular.\n"
"\n"
"**You** *(to the crowd)*: We have brought you a package from Implis. Here, "
"this is for you. Scribble throws it into the crowd, and the formal "
"philosophers tear it open. In fact, there is only a single piece of paper "
"inside. After a few minutes, it is back with you. And the formal "
"philosophers all look curiously at how you handle it."

