#: Game.Levels.Babylon
#, fuzzy
msgid "Intro Babylon"
msgstr ""
"You reach a planet where countless stone slabs are stacked into bizarrely "
"tall towers. The entire landscape looks like a giant jigsaw puzzle, with "
"each slab neatly built on top of the ones below. Some towers are so tall "
"that you cannot even see their tops. Soon you encounter the first inhabitant "
"of this planet.\n"
"\n"
"**Babylonian**: Welcome to *Babylon*! **You**: Oh... You get an uneasy "
"feeling.\n"
"\n"
"**You**: Are you sure these towers are stable? **Babylonian**: 100 per cent! "
"**You**: How do you build these masterpieces? **Babylonian**: It's simple! "
"One stone at a time."

#: Game.Levels.Iso
#, fuzzy
msgid "Intro Iso"
msgstr ""
"**You**: Look, another planet with two skyscrapers! **Scribble**: Yes, but "
"these ones are the same height. Now I don't know where to land. **You**: "
"People are waving on the left! So land on the left. But the reception there "
"is rather poor.\n"
"\n"
"**Isosoph**: Good day! It's not very polite to land here in the middle of "
"the crowd! We marked a landing site over there especially for you! "
"**Scribble**: Sorry! I didn't recognise the symbolism. **Isosoph**: That "
"went well! We had already heard that you were a little different. "
"Nevertheless, we'll show you our ingenious transport system – the most "
"advanced local transport system in the entire Formaloversum! As it turns "
"out, one of the particularly advanced aspects is that the transport capsules "
"on this planet can be used in both directions. You dash back and forth a few "
"times."

