msgstr ""
"**You**: I'm still shocked. I thought we were doing maths here. Why should "
"§0 be §1 again? **Scribble**: It's purely a matter of opinion.  You imagine "
"§2 as a mapping that is only defined on the positive natural numbers. In "
"Leansch, §3 is simply a mapping that is defined on all natural numbers, and "
"it sends §4 to §5. Why not? In the end, this mapping will only be applied to "
"positive numbers anyway, and fortunately your interpretation coincides with "
"Leansch's interpretation on those numbers."

